THE RISK (context, do not rewrite): perturbation [{"nodeId":"geo.NL","op":"set","value":0.18,"note":"NL flow share well below its stock share given the ban and connection cap"},{"nodeId":"geo.PL","op":"set","value":0.11,"note":"Poland absorbs a larger share of window-period additions"},{"nodeId":"geo.other","op":"set","value":0.05,"note":"CEE tail (esp. Romania) takes redirected flow; net effect is a modest TAM haircut plus a mix shift"}], likelihood 0.62, category model-structure

FIELDS TO REWRITE:
{
 "title": "The geo split is a museum exhibit: NL's 0.28 is installed stock, but Year-1 revenue lives in the flow — which the Dutch hyperscale ban has already redirected",
 "narrative": "Every geo ratio is derived from a 2025 installed-colocation snapshot. But a pre-launch entrant sells into new fit-outs and expansions — the flow — and the flow map looks nothing like the stock map. Since early 2024 the Netherlands bans new hyperscale data centres outside two municipalities, Amsterdam's connections are capped, and even the DC Byte commentary notes development activity has structurally slowed with 'other markets offering strong alternatives.' Meanwhile investment is shifting to regional hubs and eastward. Weighting Year-1 sales coverage, certification sequencing, and channel hires by a 0.28 NL share systematically points the venture at the geography where the least new PDU-consuming capacity will be commissioned during its window.",
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "An amended decree bans new hyperscale data centres (70+ MW) in the Netherlands outside Het Hogeland and Hollands Kroon since early 2024, and Amsterdam's draft zoning plan caps new connections at 350 MVA until 2030 — the NL new-build flow is administratively foreclosed, not merely slow",
   "refs": [
    "digest:geo-NL#c7",
    "digest:geo-NL#c8"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "Cushman & Wakefield reports Amsterdam at 852 MW with 'less room for further expansion, while investment is more quickly shifting to other European hubs and to regional locations'; DC Byte notes post-moratorium development runs at a reduced rate — so CE fit-out flow reallocates toward Germany, Poland and the CEE tail while NL's installed stock keeps its 28% weight in the model",
   "refs": [
    "digest:geo-NL#c0",
    "digest:geo-NL#c16",
    "ledger:geo.NL"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "For a first-12-months entrant, PDU demand is proportional to commissioned/expanded capacity in the window, not to standing stock; geo.NL's 0.28 overstates the NL slice of orderable demand while geo.PL (0.07) and geo.other (0.03) — where the derivations already flag divergent, faster-growing scopes — understate theirs",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:geo.PL",
    "ledger:geo.other",
    "profile:Stage"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The NL node looks like the model's safest: triangulated, two sources agreeing within 3%. That agreement is precisely the trap — both sources measure the same stock quantity, and stock is the wrong quantity for a Year-1 revenue model. A number can be perfectly sourced and still be the answer to a different question.",
 "falsifier": "DDA's 2026 State of the Dutch Data Centers (or Statista's 2026 update) showing NL colocation MW additions at or above 28% of total CE-7 additions for the year.",
 "likelihoodRationale": "The hyperscale ban, the Amsterdam connection cap, and C&W's explicit 'investment shifting' statement are all in force today; the uncertainty is magnitude (retrofit and the two exempt municipalities keep some NL flow alive), not direction. [evidence revision: The ban's legal force and the flow-reallocation direction are strongly and independently corroborated, and DDA 2026 shows NL growth (7%/12% CAGR) trailing the European average — consistent with the falsifier not being met. Modest upward revision from 0.55; magnitude uncertainty remains because the two exempt municipalities, regional NL hubs (Groningen/South Holland/North Brabant), and retrofit still keep meaningful NL colocation flow alive, and precise NL-vs-CE-7 additions shares were not quantified in the results.]"
}

